# RULE 02 — RESPOND BEFORE CODING

Before generating ANY code on a new block, Cursor MUST first respond with this exact format and WAIT for Jorge to acknowledge before continuing:

```
Spec sources reviewed:
- docs/specs/CURSOR-PERMANENT-RULES.md
- docs/specs/IH35_MASTER_BLUEPRINT_v3_FULL.md (sections: [list])
- docs/specs/IH35_UNIFIED_BLUEPRINT_ADDITIONS.md (sections: [list])
- docs/specs/IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md (modules: [list])

Approved screens reviewed:
- docs/approved-screens/[filename.png]
- [add more if multiple]

Tab count check:
- Module: [name]
- Architectural design says: [N tabs]
- Current code has: [N tabs]
- This block changes count to: [N tabs] (✅ matches design / ⚠️ design needs update in this commit)

Deviations from spec required (with rationale):
- [list any deviation, or write "None"]

NEW SPEC items (in this block but not in either spec source):
- [list with rationale, or write "None"]

Proceeding.
```

## Exception

For pure file-renaming, doc-only commits, or trivial typo fixes that don't touch code logic, Cursor may skip the spec-review block but MUST still note in the commit message that the change is doc-only or rename-only.

## Why this rule exists

Cursor was generating code without first checking what the architectural design said the module should contain. This caused Safety to ship missing 4 tabs (Fines, Company Violations, Liabilities cross-link, Integrity Alerts) — exactly the patch-on-patch failure mode Jorge is preventing.

The respond-before-code gate forces a moment of explicit verification. If the spec review reveals a gap, Cursor pauses and asks rather than building partial work.
